Source: datasketches
Section: database
Priority: optional
Maintainer: Ruohang Feng <rh@vonng.com>
Build-Depends: debhelper-compat (= 13), postgresql-all (>= 217~), unzip, g++, libboost-dev
Standards-Version: 4.6.2
Rules-Requires-Root: no
Homepage: https://github.com/apache/datasketches-postgresql

Package: postgresql-PGVERSION-datasketches
Architecture: any
Provides: postgresql-datasketches
Depends: ${postgresql:Depends}, ${shlibs:Depends}, ${misc:Depends}
Description: Apache DataSketches extension for approximate analytics in PostgreSQL
 Apache DataSketches brings approximate analytics data types and aggregates to
 PostgreSQL. The extension includes CPC, HLL, Theta, Array-of-Doubles, KLL,
 REQ, quantiles, and frequent-strings sketches for fast approximate distinct
 counting, quantiles, histograms, and heavy-hitter analysis.
